(TodoAppWasm Auth and JWT Guide) Tj
T*
(Junior developer reference for tasks 034_backend_auth_user_accounts and 035_backend_jwt_authorization.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Big Picture) Tj
T*
(Task 034 teaches the backend how to register and login users safely.) Tj
T*
(Task 035 adds JWT tokens so the backend can protect Todo endpoints and know which user is making each request.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Before authentication, the client could send ownerId in JSON and the backend trusted it.) Tj
T*
(After JWT authorization, the backend reads the real logged-in user id from the token.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Task 034 - User Accounts and Password Hashing) Tj
T*
(Goal: users register with a password, but the password is never stored as plain text.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(User model change:) Tj
T*
(  public string PasswordHash { get; set; } = string.Empty;) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why: The database stores PasswordHash instead of Password. If someone opens the database, they should not see real passwords.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(UserCreationDto change:) Tj
T*
(  public string UserName { get; set; }) Tj
T*
(  public string Password { get; set; }) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why: Registration needs username and password from Swagger or the frontend.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Password hashing service:) Tj
T*
(  Pbkdf2PasswordHasher.Hash\(password\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What it does:) Tj
T*
(  - creates a random salt) Tj
T*
(  - derives a secure key from the password and salt) Tj
T*
(  - stores algorithm, iterations, salt, and key together) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important: Hashing is one-way. We do not decrypt passwords. On login, we hash the entered password again and compare hashes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Password verification:) Tj
T*
(  passwordHasher.Verify\(dto.Password, existing.PasswordHash\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why FixedTimeEquals is used: it avoids leaking tiny timing clues about the hash comparison.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(UserLogic registration:) Tj
T*
(  UserName = usertoCreate.UserName) Tj
T*
(  PasswordHash = passwordHasher.Hash\(usertoCreate.Password\)) Tj
T*
(  Role = UserRoles.User) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
