(  app.UseAuthorization\(\);) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why order matters:) Tj
T*
(  UseAuthentication reads the token and creates User.Claims.) Tj
T*
(  UseAuthorization checks if the endpoint can run.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Swagger Bearer setup:) Tj
T*
(  Swagger needs AddSecurityDefinition and AddSecurityRequirement to show the Authorize button.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How to paste token in Swagger:) Tj
T*
(  Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Roles vs Ownership) Tj
T*
(Roles are account types. Examples: User, Admin.) Tj
T*
(Ownership is about one specific todo. Example: todo.OwnerId == loggedInUserId.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Clean rule:) Tj
T*
(  Admin and User are roles.) Tj
T*
(  Owner is not a role.) Tj
T*
(  Owner is checked by comparing Todo.OwnerId with the user id from the JWT token.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Protected Todo Endpoints) Tj
T*
(TodosController has [Authorize], so users must login before calling Todo endpoints.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Create Todo:) Tj
T*
(  int userId = GetCurrentUserId\(\);) Tj
T*
(  TodoCreationDto secureDto = new\(userId, dto.Title, dto.Description\);) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why: The API no longer trusts ownerId from JSON. It uses the user id from the JWT token.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(List Todos:) Tj
T*
(  Admin can inspect broader data.) Tj
T*
(  Normal users only see their own todos.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Access check:) Tj
T*
(  If Admin OR todo.OwnerId equals current user id, allow access.) Tj
T*
(  Otherwise return 404.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why 404 instead of 403: it avoids revealing that another user's todo exists.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. How to Test in Swagger) Tj
T*
(1. Apply migrations so Users table has PasswordHash and Role.) Tj
T*
(2. Create a user with POST /Users.) Tj
T*
(3. Login with POST /Users/login.) Tj
T*
ET
